---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

export const title = "Cannabis Cultivation Guide";
---

<Layout 
  title="Cannabis Cultivation Guide | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Complete guide to cannabis cultivation in Maine. Licensing, growing operations, and regulations for commercial growers."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1589829545856-d10d557cf95f?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Cannabis Cultivation Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Starting a commercial cannabis grow operation in Maine</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Cannabis cultivation—growing cannabis for commercial sale—is the foundation of the cannabis supply chain. Maine's favorable climate and established agricultural community make it an excellent <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-locations/">location</a> for cultivators. Whether you're interested in indoor, greenhouse, or outdoor growing, understanding the licensing and operational requirements is essential. Before moving forward, familiarize yourself with the <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-license/">licensing process</a> essential for success.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Excellence in Compliance" type="success">
      Mastering this aspect of your business is a badge of professional excellence. It ensures longevity and demonstrates your commitment to the highest standards of the Maine cannabis industry.
    </Callout>


    <section>
      <h2>License Types</h2>
      <p>Under <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine OCP regulations</a>, cultivation licenses include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cultivation Facility</strong> - Large-scale commercial growing</li>
        <li><strong>Micro- Cultivation</strong> - Smaller scale operation</li>
        <li><strong>Home Cultivation</strong> - Limited personal grows (not for sale)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Growing Methods</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Indoor</strong> - Year-round, full control, higher energy costs</li>
        <li><strong>Greenhouse</strong> - Natural light with climate control</li>
        <li><strong>Outdoor</strong> - Lowest cost, seasonal, weather dependent</li>
        <li><strong>Hybrid</strong> - Combination approach</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Facility Requirements</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Proper <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-real-estate/">zoning</a> (agricultural or industrial)</li>
        <li>Security systems and video surveillance</li>
        <li>Climate control (HVAC, humidity)</li>
        <li>Lighting systems (if indoor)</li>
        <li>Water and irrigation systems</li>
        <li>Odor control</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Compliance Requirements</h2>
      <p>Maine requires:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Seed-to-sale tracking (<a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-inventory-management/">METRC</a> or similar)</li>
        <li>Testing of all products</li>
        <li>Secure storage</li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-staffing-licensing/">Employee licensing</a></li>
        <li>Detailed record keeping</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Investment Overview</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>Estimated Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Indoor Facility (5,000 sq ft)</td><td>$200,000-500,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Greenhouse</td><td>$100,000-300,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Equipment</td><td>$50,000-200,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Licensing</td><td>$5,000-15,000</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine Cannabis Rules</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Consult with qualified professionals.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
